    "description": "Retrieves all ad sets matching conditions set in the filter (also referred to as campaigns)\r\nThis method should be called by the agent whenever\r\nit needs information about one or more ad sets.\r\nIt provides a comprehensive list of ad sets with key metadata and status fields.\r\n\r\nReturns:\r\n-------\r\nResponse\r\n    An object containing data with the following information for each ad set:\r\n    - id: The unique identifier of the ad set (also called Campaign ID).\r\n    - name: The name of the ad set.\r\n    - advertiserId: The ID of the advertiser that owns this ad set.\r\n    - objective (MarketingObjective): The marketing objective associated with the ad set: Acquisition or Retention.\r\n    - startDate: The start date of the ad set, if specified.\r\n    - activationStatus: Indicates whether the ad set is currently active: Activated or NotActivated\r\n    - deliveryStatus: Describes the current delivery state of the ad set: Running, Archived or NotRunning\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\n-----\r\nUse this method as the primary source for retrieving ad set (campaign) information.",
