    "type": "function",
    "name": "get_custom_report",
    "description": "Calls the API to retrieve client data.\r\n\r\nArgs:\r\n    filters: An object containing the built-in filters.\r\n        Default values are provided if needed.\r\n    timeDimension: Time-based dimension for data projections; specifies the granularity at which data will be grouped.\r\n        Possible values and examples:\r\n            - None: Indicates that the user has not provided any clear time dimension.\r\n                This should be selected when there is no explicit instruction.\r\n                Do NOT infer or assume a value; use None unless the user specifies otherwise.\r\n            - Year: Represents a calendar year.\r\n                Examples: per year, by year, year-over-year comparisons (YoY), yearly trend analysis.\r\n            - Month: Represents a calendar month.\r\n                Examples: per month, by month, month-over-month comparisons (MoM), monthly performance reports.\r\n            - Week: Represents a calendar week.\r\n                Examples: per week, by week, week-over-week comparisons (WoW), weekly campaign summaries.\r\n            - Day: Represents a calendar day.\r\n                Examples: per day, by day, day-over-day comparisons (DoD), daily performance tracking.\r\n            - Hour: Represents an hour within a day.\r\n                Examples: per hour, by hour, hourly trend analysis, intraday performance monitoring.\r\n    dimensions: A list of dimensions that define the granularity of the report.\r\n        Example: [os, device]\r\n    metrics: A list of performance indicators to retrieve.\r\n        Example: [clicks, ctr]\r\n    attributionModel: Specifies the model used to measure sales.\r\n        Optional.\r\n    additionalFilters: Custom filters applied to the data.\r\n        CRITICAL CONSTRAINT: Every dimension used in \u0060additionalFilters\u0060 MUST be present in the \u0060dimensions\u0060 list.\r\n        If a filter references a dimension not included in \u0060dimensions\u0060, the request will be rejected.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\n    - Dimensions determine the level of detail in the report.\r\n    - Metrics represent the KPIs to monitor campaign performance.\r\n    - Filters restrict the dataset retrieved from the API.\r\n    - \u0060additionalFilters\u0060 allow for extra filtering, but only on dimensions explicitly listed in \u0060dimensions\u0060.",
    "parameters": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "filters": {
          "description": "Filters are a way to narrow the scope of the report by setting certain values.\r\nIf no value can be inferred, a default one will be provided.",
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "clientIds": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "integer"
              }
            },
            "dateRange": {
              "description": "Date range between two dates.\r\nIMPORTANT: from_date and to_date are inclusive (the start and end dates are included in the period).\r\n\r\nIf dates are not given explicitly, they can be deduced as follows:\r\n\r\n- IMPORTANT: Last n days: from = today - n days, to = yesterday (inclusive, does not include today)\r\n    Example: if today is 2025-08-23 then \u0022last 7 days\u0022: 2025-08-16 to 2025-08-22 (inclusive, 7 days)\r\n    Example: if today is 2025-08-10 then \u0022last 20 days\u0022: 2025-07-21 to 2025-08-09 (inclusive, 20 days)\r\n- Month of May 2025: from = 2025-05-01, to = 2025-05-31\r\n- IMPORTANT: Last week, the last full calendar week (Monday to Sunday) before the current Week:\r\n    from = Monday of previous week\r\n    to = Sunday of previous Week\r\n    Example: if today is Tuesday, 2025-08-12 then \u0022last week\u0022 is Monday 2025-08-04 to Sunday 2025-08-10\r\n    Example: if today is Monday, 2025-09-15 then \u0022last week\u0022 is Monday 2025-08-14 to Sunday 2025-08-14\r\n- IMPORTANT: Last n weeks, the last n full calendar weeks (Monday to Sunday) before the current Week.\r\n    n is the number of weeks.\r\n    from = Monday of n weeks ago\r\n    to = Sunday of previous Week\r\n    Example: if today is Friday, 2025-08-22 then \u0022last 2 weeks\u0022 is\r\n        Monday 2025-08-04 to Sunday 2025-08-17\r\n        n is 2\r\n    Example: if today is Monday, 2025-07-21 then \u0022last 3 weeks\u0022 is\r\n        Monday 2025-06-30 to Sunday 2025-07-20\r\n        n is 3\r\n- IMPORTANT: Last month, the last full calendar month before the current month.\r\n    from = first day of previous month\r\n    to = last day of previous month\r\n    Example: if today is Tuesday, 2025-08-19 then \u0022last month\u0022 is 2025-07-01 to 2025-07-31\r\n- IMPORTANT: Last n months, the last n full calendar months before the current month.\r\n    n is the number of months.\r\n    from = first day of the month n months ago\r\n    to = last day of previous month\r\n    Example: if today is Monday, 2025-08-19 then \u0022last 3 months\u0022 is 2025-05-01 to 2025-07-31\r\n        n is 3\r\n- Last quarter: the last full quarter before the current quarter.\r\n    Q1: January 1 to March 31\r\n    Q2: April 1 to June 30\r\n    Q3: July 1 to September 30\r\n    Q4: October 1 to December 31\r\n\r\n\r\ntime_zone is the IANA time zone name (e.g., \u0022Europe/London\u0022, \u0022America/New_York\u0022).\r\nBy default, assume that we are in the Europe/London time zone.\r\n\r\nThe field previous_period_from_date is used to define the starting date of a previous period\r\nthat mirrors the current data collection range.\r\nThis allows for comparative analysis between the current period and a similar past period.\r\n\r\nUse the following guidelines and examples to determine the correct value:\r\n\r\nGeneral Rule:\r\nprevious_period_from_date should be set to a date that starts the previous comparable period\r\nthe previous period will have the same duration as the current one\r\nthe previous period and the current period MUST NOT overlap\r\n\r\n    Examples:\r\n    Relative Time Comparison\r\n        If comparing to last year, and from_date = 2025-08-01, then:\r\n            previous_period_from_date = 2024-08-01\r\n        If comparing with the previous period, previous_period_start_date is calculated\r\n        by subtracting the duration of the current date range from its starting date (from_date).\r\n        This ensures the previous period has the same length and ends\r\n        right before the current one begins.\r\n        Example:\r\n            Current range: from_date = 2025-08-10, to_date = 2025-08-19 (10 days including bounds),\r\n            then: previous_period_start_date = 2025-07-31 (10 days before 2025-08-10)\r\n    Custom Period Comparison\r\n        If comparing to the period starting 2025-02-25, then:\r\n            previous_period_from_date = 2025-02-25\r\n",
              "type": "object",
              "properties": {
                "from_date": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "format": "date"
                },
                "to_date": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "format": "date"
