        "timeDimension": {
          "description": "Defines the time-based dimensions available for data projections.\r\n\r\nEach enum member specifies the granularity at which data can be grouped or analyzed.\r\n\r\nMembers:\r\n    None  - Indicates that the user has not provided any clear time dimension.\r\n        This should be selected when there is no explicit instruction.\r\n        Do NOT infer or assume a value; use None unless the user specifies otherwise.\r\n    Year  - Represents a calendar year. For example per year, by year, year-over-year comparisons (YoY), yearly trend analysis.\r\n    Month - Represents a calendar month. For example per month, by month, month-over-month comparisons (MoM), monthly performance reports.\r\n    Week  - Represents a calendar week. For example per week, by week, week-over-week comparisons (WoW), weekly campaign summaries.\r\n    Day   - Represents a calendar day. For example per day, by day, day-over-day comparisons (DoD), daily performance tracking.\r\n    Hour  - Represents an hour within a day. For example per hour, by hour, hourly trend analysis, intraday performance monitoring.",
