        "attributionModel": {
          "description": "    Attribution models define how sales are credited to advertising campaigns.\r\n\r\n    Available models:\r\n\r\n        Pv1d: 1-Day Post View\r\n        \u2014 Sale is attributed when a user views an ad and purchases within 24 hours.\r\n\r\n        Pc1d: 1-Day Post Click\r\n        \u2014 Sale is attributed when a user clicks an ad and purchases within 24 hours.\r\n\r\n        Pc7d: 7-Day Post Click\r\n        \u2014 Sale is attributed when a user clicks an ad and purchases within 7 days.\r\n\r\n        Pv7d: 7-Day Post View\r\n        \u2014 Sale is attributed when a user views an ad and purchases within 7 days.\r\n\r\n        Pv14d: 14-Day Post View\r\n        \u2014 Sale is attributed when a user views an ad and purchases within 14 days.\r\n\r\n        Pv30d: 30-Day Post View\r\n        \u2014 Sale is attributed when a user views an ad and purchases within 30 days.\r\n\r\n        Pc30d: 30-Day Post Click\r\n        \u2014 Sale is attributed when a user clicks an ad and purchases within 30 days.\r\n\r\n        Pc30dPv1d: 30-Day Post Click \u002B 1-Day Post View\r\n        \u2014 Sale is attributed if a user clicks and purchases within 30 days, or views and purchases within 24 hours.\r\n\r\n        Pc7dPv1d: 7-Day Post Click \u002B 1-Day Post View\r\n        \u2014 Sale is attributed if a user clicks and purchases within 7 days, or views and purchases within 24 hours.\r\n\r\n        Lc30d: Last Click\r\n        \u2014 Full credit is given to the last click before a conversion.\r\n\r\n        CAttr: Client Attribution\r\n        \u2014 Attribution is determined by the advertiser using Criteo\u0027s deduplication parameter.",
          "type": "string",
          "enum": [
