  {
    "type": "function",
    "name": "final_result",
    "description": "The final response which ends this conversation. ALWAYS use this tool to return your answer.",
    "parameters": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "input": {
          "description": "Represents the response generated by an agent after processing a user request.\r\nAny tables and graphs will be generated using data from the internal conversation state.\r\n\r\nThere is no need to explicitly pass the tabular data from any tool as contents of the\r\n\u0060comment\u0060 property. Thus, never generate a markdown table as part of the \u0060comment\u0060 field.\r\n\r\nFields:\r\n    comment:\r\n        A textual response generated by the agent, adhering to the instructions provided in the conversation\r\n\r\n    response_status:\r\n        A classification of the response outcome, indicating how the agent handled the request.\r\n    follow_up_questions:\r\n        A short list of 2\u20133 suggestions for further exploration of the data.",
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "comment": {
              "description": "A structured explanation accompanying the agent\u0027s response.\r\n\r\nIf the agent successfully answered the question:\r\n- Provides a **summary** of the result.\r\n- Offers a **brief explanation** of key concepts or logic used.\r\n\r\nIf the agent failed to answer:\r\n- Describes the **problem encountered** (e.g., missing data, ambiguous query).\r\n- Explains the **reason for failure** to help the user understand what went wrong.\r\n\r\nNote:\r\nThis field should **never include the full requested data**.\r\nThat will be provided separately.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\nQuestion: What was the total spend for each campaign in May 2025?\r\n\r\nSummary: The total spend for all campaigns in May 2025 was 1,240,391.25.\r\n\r\nExplanation: \u0027Spend\u0027 or \u0027Cost\u0027 refers to the total amount of money invested\r\nin an advertising campaign during a specified period.\r\nIt\u0027s a direct measure of your advertising expenditure.",
              "type": "string"
